urfer</author> <category>Business</category> <category>topic/business</category> <category>topic/deep-dives</category> <category>topic/indian-markets</category> <description>An in-depth analysis of India&#39;s datacenter landscape, exploring the current state, challenges, and future prospects of the country&#39;s AI and data infrastructure.</description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/08/31/business-of-datacenters---an-india-perspective/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2024 12:33:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/08/31/business-of-datacenters---an-india-perspective/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Tech Tip - My WSL2 devsetup for terminal productivity</title> <category>Engineering</category> <category>topic/devtools</category> <category>topic/techtips</category> <category>topic/wsl2</category> <description>Here are some tips to make your Windows devloper machine experience as close to a linux box. We cover terminal, neovim, Xserver applications and networking in WSL2 to make your life easy.</description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/08/14/tech-tip---my-wsl2-devsetup-for-terminal-productivity/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2024 12:22:51 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/08/14/tech-tip---my-wsl2-devsetup-for-terminal-productivity/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Tech Tip - Make Neovim Python LSP play nice with pyenv</title> <category>Engineering</category> <category>topic/devtools</category> <category>topic/engineering</category> <category>topic/neovim</category> <category>topic/python</category> <description>Modern python development relies on some form of virtual environment management. pyenv + virtialenv is a goto toolkit for managing both python versions and isolated package environments. For people using Neovim as their editor, setting up Neovim&#39;s LSP to play nice with pyenv requires a trick. This post covers the interplay of tools to make this work.</description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/07/26/tech-tip---make-neovim-python-lsp-play-nice-with-pyenv/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Fri, 26 Jul 2024 02:11:58 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/07/26/tech-tip---make-neovim-python-lsp-play-nice-with-pyenv/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Home</title> <description></description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Jul 2024 15:07:31 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Ghost in a shell - What the heck is a Terminal/Shell/TTY?</title> <category>Engineering</category> <category>series/bits-n-bytes</category> <category>topic/deep-dives</category> <category>topic/devops</category> <category>topic/platform-engineering</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Ghost in a shell - What the heck is a Terminal/Shell/TTY?&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Long ago, in the early days of computing, when machines were vast and mysterious entities hidden behind layers of complexity, the world of Unix was emerging. It was a time when interactions with these computing behemoths were facilitated by peculiar devices known as terminals.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/04/07/ghost-in-a-shell---what-the-heck-is-a-terminalshelltty/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Jul 2024 15:07:31 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/04/07/ghost-in-a-shell---what-the-heck-is-a-terminalshelltty/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Rise of Internal Developer Portals (iDp) - Part 1</title> <category>Engineering</category> <category>topic/devops</category> <category>topic/platform-engineering</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Rise of Internal Developer Portals (iDp) - Part 1&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;In today&#39;s rapidly evolving software development landscape, staying ahead of the curve is crucial for success. One emerging trend that has gained significant traction is the adoption of Internal Developer Portals (iDp). &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/04/18/rise-of-internal-developer-portals-idp---part-1/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Jul 2024 15:07:31 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.shaishav.kr/feed_rss_created.xml">wiresurfer's library | © shaishav.kr</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.shaishav.kr/2024/04/18/rise-of-internal-developer-portals-idp---part-1/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>